{"summary":"To set up the CAMEL project from source, follow these steps: Clone the repository using `git clone https://github.com/camel-ai/camel.git`, then change into the project directory. Activate the virtual environment with `poetry shell` and install dependencies with `poetry install --with dev,docs` or `poetry install --with dev,docs -E all` to include all extra packages.

After installation, configure pre-commit hooks using `pre-commit install` and verify everything by running `pytest .` for all tests.

For running tests that may require an OpenAI API key, create a `.env` file in the root directory containing your API key and optionally the base URL. Use `pytest --fast-test-mode .` for local isolated unit and integration tests."}
